%PAGE
{{endnote placement-of-squares}}
Placement of Squares on Triangle in S._M.

As the Candidate(s) visibility of this action is limited and brief, the
exact placement is unlikely to matter much: [[strong]][[underline]]H._K._T. and H._A. should simply
conform to the placement chosen by S. K. I.[[/underline]][[/strong]] As a matter of consideration, here
are four apparent ways in which the Three Master's Jewels (Squares) may be
placed upon the edges of the Triangle:

%IMAGE "figures/e308-placement-of-squares.png" 18

Method 1, with all arms of the Squares extending into the Triangle, is specified in
the 2018 Provisional Ritual of the General Grand Council. Method 2, with squares
held in the left hand applied to the edges of the triangle to form perpendiculars,
would seem to allude to the way in which the R. A. word is communicated, and is
specified in the 2015 Ritual of the Grand Council of Iowa. Method 3, with the
arms extending out from the midst of the Triangle, may best illustrate the
relationship between the Cover Words and the I. N. O. D. Method 4 may allude
generally to the idea of covering or concealing:

%SPACE 0.1in
%COLUMN 0.5in 0
It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings is to
search out a matter. —Proverbs 25:2.
%COLUMN OFF
%SPACE 0.1in

More interesting than the specific placement is the fact that this action is at odds
with the legend presented in the Royal Arch Degree, where the squares are
discovered upon penetrating the Arch and descending into the Vault, but before the
sun at meridian height allowed for discovery of either the Ark or Pedestal. This
difference is owing to the separate historical transmission of this degree.

